<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>FAQs</title>
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-gray-100 font-sans">
    <%- include('partials/header', { title: 'FAQs' }) %>
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-12 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-center font-serif mb-8">FAQs</h1>
      <p class="" class="text-gray-600 mb-10 text-center">
        Frequently Asked Questions.<br />Here are some common questions about
        Note Vault.
      </p>

      <div class="divide-y divide-gray-300">
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">What is Note Vault?</h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              Note Vault is a secure application for storing and managing your
              notes safely in one place.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">How do I create a new note?</h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              To create a new note, click on the "New Note" button in your
              dashboard and start typing your content. Save it once you're done.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">Is my data secure?</h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              Yes, Note Vault uses advanced encryption methods to ensure that
              your data is always secure and private.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">Can I access my notes offline?</h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              Currently, Note Vault requires an internet connection to access
              your notes, but offline access is a feature we are working on.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">
              How do I share my notes with others?
            </h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              You can share your notes by clicking the "Share" button and
              entering the email address of the person you want to share with.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">
              How do I recover a deleted note?
            </h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              Deleted notes are moved to the "Trash" folder. You can recover a
              note by going to the Trash folder and restoring it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">
              What should I do if I forget my password?
            </h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              If you forget your password, click on the "Forgot Password" link
              on the login page and follow the instructions to reset it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item py-4">
          <div
            class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer">
            <h5 class="text-lg font-medium">
              Can I organize my notes into folders?
            </h5>
            <span class="text-xl font-bold">+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden pl-6 mt-2">
            <p class="">
              Yes, you can organize your notes into folders for better
              management. Use the "Create Folder" option to start organizing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <%- include("partials/footer") %>
    <script>
      document.querySelectorAll(".faq-question").forEach((item) => {
        item.addEventListener("click", () => {
          const answer = item.nextElementSibling;
          const span = item.querySelector("span");
          answer.classList.toggle("hidden");
          span.textContent = span.textContent === "+" ? "âˆ’" : "+";
        });
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
